  "description": "An analytical sociology of how late-liberal governance reproduces itself on a contracting energetic substrate by formatting its constitutive contradictions as personally manageable affect, distributing that formatting through platformal feedback architecture, and absorbing every coherent subject-position — including those that name themselves as outsides — back into its metabolism.",
  "name": "Cybernetic Postliberalism",
